{{Infobox writer | name = Edvard Kovač | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth year and age|1950}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Theologian, philosopher and writer | nationality = | spouse = | children = | genre = | movement = | notableworks = Oddaljena bližina | awards = {{Awd|[[Rožanc Award]]|2000|for Oddaljena bližina}} | influences = | influenced = | website = | footnotes = }}
Fr. '''Edvard Kovač''' (born 1950) is a [[Slovenia]]n [[theologian]], [[philosopher]] and [[author]]. He is a member of the [[Franciscan|Order of Friars Minor]] and professor at the [[University of Ljubljana |University of Ljubljana Theological Faculty]] and the [[Catholic University of Toulouse]].<ref>[http://www.teof.uni-lj.si/?viewPage=153&action=view&id=30 Ljubljana Theological Faculty site]</ref>
Kovač is author of numerous published works and has twice been awarded the French [[Ordre national du Mérite|Ordre du Mérite]].<ref>[http://www.rtvslo.si/kultura/drugo/edvard-kovac-prejme-red-za-zasluge/151083 RTVSLO.si - ''Edvard Kovač prejme Red za zasluge'' Edvard Kovač receives Order of Merit]</ref><ref>[http://www.rtvslo.si/kultura/drugo/francija-odlikovala-slovenske-viteze-reda-umetnosti-in-leposlovja/268873 RTVSLO.si - ''Francija odlikovala slovenske viteze reda umetnosti in leposlovja'' France Honours Slovene Knights of the Order of Merit in Arts and Literature]</ref> In 2000 he received the [[Rožanc Award]] (the most prestigious Slovenian award for essayism) for his collection of essays ''Oddaljena bližina'' (The Distant Proximity).
His thought has been influenced by the Jewish theologians [[Emmanuel Levinas]] and [[Martin Buber]], the [[Christian existentialism]] of [[Gabriel Marcel]] and by the French [[Nouvelle Théologie]].
==Published works== * ''Nietzschejeva tragičnost'' (The Tragedy of Nietzsche), 1980 * ''Slovenska nacionalna zavest'' (Slovene National Conscience), 1992 (with [[Franc Rode]]) * ''Modrost o ljubezni'' (Wisdom on Love), 1992 * ''Oddaljena bližina'' (The Distant Proximity), 2000
